Create an Account on PyPI
Register at https://pypi.org/account/register/.

Ensure your package is ready to be distributed. You can do this by running:
>> python setup.py sdist bdist_wheel

Upload to PyPI
Install twine: If you haven't installed twine, do so using pip:
>> pip install twine

>>> twine upload dist/*
You will be prompted to enter your PyPI username and password.

Verify and Test
After uploading, your package should be visible on PyPI. You can test the installation by creating a virtual environment and installing your package:

>> python -m venv test_env
>> source test_env/bin/activate  # On Windows, use `test_env\Scripts\activate`
>> pip install pyZink